reviews.review_text: Jack Straw for the ages Yes, the show is sloppy. A few songs, MNS and Dancin, are verifiable train wrecks though still with some smoke to them. But do yourself a favor and blast that Jack Straw to open the second set. To my experienced ears, that's the best version of that song I've ever heard, bar none. Enjoy

Jack Straw Always interested to hear recommendations for great Straws. Well, we all hear these things with different ears... it's nice, but for me doesn't match 22/1/78 for sheer ferocity, or 11/1/79 for being totally mental. Still good though, thanks.
They can't all be winners Not miserable, but not great. They try to make up for it with a long first set, Jack Straw, and Black Peter. Just okay.
